Author: Bibi
Ingredients: [{'ingredient': 'seafood stock', 'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'unsalted butter', 'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'misc': 'divided'}, {'ingredient': 'shallot', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': 'minced'}, {'ingredient': 'arborio rice', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'misc': '16 ounce'}, {'ingredient': 'thyme', 'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'sprigs', 'misc': 'fresh'}, {'ingredient': 'garlic', 'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'misc': 'minced'}, {'ingredient': 'white wine', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': 'dry'}, {'ingredient': 'lemon juice', 'quantity': '0.25', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'and black pepper to taste', 'quantity': '', 'unit': 'salt', 'misc': 'ground'}, {'ingredient': 'shrimp - and deveined', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'misc': 'tails left intact uncooked medium peeled'}, {'ingredient': 'lemon zest', 'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'parmesan cheese', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': 'grated'}]
Ingredients_Raw: ['4 cups seafood stock', '3 tablespoons unsalted butter, divided', '0.5 cup minced shallot', '1 (16 ounce) package Arborio rice', '3 sprigs fresh thyme', '2 cloves garlic, minced', '0.5 cup dry white wine', '0.25 cup lemon juice', 'salt and ground black pepper to taste', '1 pound uncooked medium shrimp - peeled and deveined, tails left intact', '2 teaspoons lemon zest', '0.5 cup grated Parmesan cheese']
Instructions: ['Heat seafood stock in a microwave until hot, about 5 minutes, and leave in the microwave until ready to use.', 'Turn on a multi-functional pressure cooker (such as Instant Pot®) and select Saute function  melt 2 tablespoons butter. Add shallot and cook, stirring, about 1 minute. Add rice, thyme sprigs, and garlic  cook, stirring frequently, about 2 minutes. Stir in wine and cook until the wine evaporates, about 1 minute, then stir in the hot seafood stock and lemon juice. Stir any browned bits from the bottom of the inner pot into the liquid. Add salt and pepper.', "Turn off Saute function. Close and lock the lid. Select high pressure according to manufacturer's instructions  set timer for 5 minutes. Allow 10 to 15 minutes for pressure to build.", "Release pressure carefully using the quick-release method according to manufacturer's instructions, 3 to 5 minutes. Unlock and remove the lid.", 'Remove thyme sprigs and add the shrimp. Close the lid and allow the shrimp to cook on the Keep Warm setting, until the shrimp are pink and firm and starting to curl into a "C" shape, about 7 minutes. Stir in lemon zest, the remaining 1 tablespoon of butter, and the grated Parmesan cheese. Stir until the butter is melted. Serve warm.']

Author: flannery
Ingredients: [{'ingredient': 'butter', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'misc': 'divided'}, {'ingredient': 'red potatoes', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': 'diced'}, {'ingredient': 'onion', 'quantity': '1.5', 'unit': 'cups', 'misc': 'chopped'}, {'ingredient': 'eggs', 'quantity': '6', 'unit': '', 'misc': 'beaten'}, {'ingredient': 'and black pepper to taste', 'quantity': '', 'unit': 'salt', 'misc': 'ground'}, {'ingredient': 'wheat tortillas', 'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'whole', 'misc': '7 inch'}, {'ingredient': 'and crumbled turkey bacon', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'misc': 'cooked'}, {'ingredient': 'cheddar cheese', 'quantity': '1.5', 'unit': 'cups', 'misc': 'shredded low-fat'}, {'ingredient': 'avocado', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'misc': 'thinly sliced'}, {'ingredient': 'salsa', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': 'or as needed'}, {'ingredient': 'reduced-fat sour cream', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': 'or as needed'}]
Ingredients_Raw: ['1 tablespoon butter, divided', '1 cup diced red potatoes', '1.5 cups chopped onion', '6 eggs, beaten', 'salt and ground black pepper to taste', '8 (7 inch) whole wheat tortillas', '1 pound cooked and crumbled turkey bacon', '1.5 cups shredded low-fat Cheddar cheese', '1 large avocado, thinly sliced', '0.5 cup salsa, or as needed', '0.5 cup reduced-fat sour cream, or as needed']

Name: Baked Pumpkin, Sweet Potato, and Coconut Milk Soup
Author: SerenaBloom
Ingredients: [{'ingredient': 'squash', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'acorn', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'pumpkin', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'sweet potatoes', 'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'coconut milk', 'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'misc': '14 ounce'}, {'ingredient': 'chicken broth', 'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'misc': '145 ounce'}, {'ingredient': 'to taste', 'quantity': '', 'unit': 'salt', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'black pepper to taste', 'quantity': '', 'unit': 'ground', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'lime', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'misc': 'juiced'}, {'ingredient': 'ginger', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'misc': 'or to taste ground'}]
Ingredients_Raw: ['1 acorn squash', '1 medium pumpkin', '2 large sweet potatoes', '2 (14 ounce) cans coconut milk', '2 (14.5 ounce) cans chicken broth', 'salt to taste', 'ground black pepper to taste', '1 lime, juiced', '1 pinch ground ginger, or to taste']
Instructions: ['Preheat an oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).', 'Puncture acorn squash and pumpkin in several places using a knife. Wrap the sweet potatoes in aluminum foil. Name: Italian White Bean and Sausage Stew
Author: John Mitzewich
Ingredients: [{'ingredient': 'cannellini beans', 'quantity': '1.5', 'unit': 'cups', 'misc': 'dry'}, {'ingredient': 'sausage links garlic and fennel', 'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'italian', 'misc': '6 ounce with'}, {'ingredient': 'yellow onion', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': 'chopped'}, {'ingredient': 'white wine', 'quantity': '0.33333334326744', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': 'dry'}, {'ingredient': 'black pepper', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'misc': 'freshly ground'}, {'ingredient': 'leaf', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'bay', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'red pepper flakes', 'quantity': '0.25', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'water', 'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'cups', 'misc': 'or to taste'}, {'ingredient': 'salt', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'misc': 'plus more to taste'}, {'ingredient': 'kale', 'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'misc': 'chopped'}, {'ingredient': 'extra-virgin olive oil', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'misc': 'or to taste'}, {'ingredient': 'parmigiano-reggiano cheese', 'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'misc': 'or to taste grated'}, {'ingredient': 'red pepper flakes', 'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'pinches', 'misc': ''}]
Ingredients_Raw: ['1.5 cups dry cannellini beans', '4 (6 ounce) Italian sausage links with garlic and fennel', '1 cup chopped yellow onion', '0.33333334326744 cup dry white wine', '1 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper', '1 bay leaf', '0.25 teaspoon red pepper flakes', '6 cups water, or to taste', '1 teaspoon salt, plus more to taste', '4 cups chopped kale', '1 tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil, or to taste', '6 tablespoons grated Parmigiano-Reggiano cheese, or to taste', '6 pinches red pepper flakes']
Instructions: ['Soak beans in cold water, 8 hours to overnight.', 'Drain beans and set aside.', 'Make a shallow cut, lengthwise, down center of each sausage link  peel off casings. Transfer bulk sausage to a dry soup pot over medium-high heat. Brown sausage, while breaking it up into small pieces with a wooden spoon, 5 to 7 minutes. Cook and stir until juices start to caramelize and stick to bottom of the pot, creating a fond, 3 to 5 minutes.', 'Add onion  stir to coat in rendered drippings. Cook until onion starts to turn translucent, about 5 minutes. Add white wine to the pot while scraping the browned bits of food off the bottom of the pot with a wooden spoon. Season with black pepper, bay leaves, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper flakes. Stir in water.', 'Add beans to the pot, increase heat to high, and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low  simmer for 30 minutes. Season with 1 teaspoon salt  simmer until beans are tender, about 30 minutes more. Taste beans to be certain they are perfectly cooked.', 'Smash about 1/4 beans with a potato masher for a creamy texture if desired. Stir in kale, increase heat to medium, and cook until tender, 10 to 15 minutes. Ingredients_Raw: ['3.5 cups all-purpose flour', '0.5 teaspoon salt', '0.5 teaspoon baking soda', '2.5 cups white sugar', '1.5 cups unsalted butter, softened', '4 large eggs', '1 cup buttermilk', '1 teaspoon lemon extract', "2 cups confectioners' sugar", '0.25 cup lemon juice', '2 tablespoons unsalted butter, softened', '1 tablespoon lemon zest']
Instructions: ['Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease and flour a fluted tube pan (such as Bundt).', 'To make the cake: Sift flour, salt, and baking soda together in a bowl.', 'Beat sugar and butter in a bowl with an electric mixer for 10 minutes. Let cool for 20 minutes, then pour remaining glaze over top.']

Ingredients_Raw: ['2 tablespoons butter', '1 onion, finely diced', 'salt to taste', '4 cups chicken broth', '2 cups water', '2 pounds fresh asparagus, trimmed and cut into 1-inch pieces', '1 pinch cayenne pepper, or to taste', 'freshly ground black pepper to taste', '1 pinch ground nutmeg', '0.5 cup heavy whipping cream', '0.25 cup heavy whipping cream', '1 tablespoon freshly grated Parmigiano-Reggiano cheese', '1 teaspoon lemon zest', '1 pinch cayenne pepper']
Instructions: ['Gather all ingredients.', 'To make the asparagus soup: Melt butter in a soup pot over medium heat. Author: friedbluetomato
Ingredients: [{'ingredient': 'self-rising flour', 'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'salt', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'unsalted butter', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': 'at room temperature'}, {'ingredient': 'white sugar', 'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'eggs', 'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'large', 'misc': 'at room temperature'}, {'ingredient': 'lemon zest', 'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'vanilla extract', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'whole milk', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': 'divided'}, {'ingredient': 'lemon juice', 'quantity': '2.5', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'misc': 'divided fresh'}, {'ingredient': 'heavy cream', 'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'misc': 'chilled'}, {'ingredient': 'confectioners sugar', 'quantity': '0.75', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'lemon juice', 'quantity': '1.5', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'misc': 'fresh'}]
Ingredients_Raw: ['3 cups self-rising flour', '0.5 teaspoon salt', '1 cup unsalted butter, at room temperature', '2 cups white sugar', '4 large eggs, at room temperature', '2 tablespoons lemon zest', '1 teaspoon vanilla extract', '1 cup whole milk, divided', '2.5 tablespoons fresh lemon juice, divided', '2 cups chilled heavy cream', "0.75 cup confectioners' sugar", '1.5 tablespoons fresh lemon juice']
Instructions: ['Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Line 30 cupcake pan cups with paper liners.', 'To make the cupcakes: Sift flour and salt together in a bowl. Beat butter and sugar together in another bowl with an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add in eggs one at a time, beating after each addition to incorporate. Mix in lemon zest and vanilla.', 'Gently beat flour mixture into butter mixture, 1/3 at a time, alternating with 1/2 of the milk and 1/2 of the lemon juice after each of the first two additions of flour. Beat until just combined  do not overmix.', 'Fill the prepared cupcake liners with batter, 3/4 full, and bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean, about 17 minutes. Name: Easy Cardamom Bread
Author: Bethany Behrle
Ingredients: [{'ingredient': 'whole milk ', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': '110 degrees f 43 degrees c warm'}, {'ingredient': 'white sugar', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'water ', 'quantity': '0.33333334326744', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': '110 degrees f 43 degrees c warm'}, {'ingredient': 'melted butter', 'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'active yeast', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'misc': '25 ounce dry'}, {'ingredient': 'all-purpose flour', 'quantity': '3.5', 'unit': 'cups', 'misc': 'or as needed'}, {'ingredient': 'cinnamon', 'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'misc': 'ground'}, {'ingredient': 'cardamom', 'quantity': '1.5', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'misc': 'ground'}, {'ingredient': 'melted butter', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'raisins', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'walnuts', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': 'chopped'}, {'ingredient': 'egg', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'water', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'almonds', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': 'sliced'}, {'ingredient': 'pearl sugar', 'quantity': '0.25', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}]
Ingredients_Raw: ['1 cup warm whole milk (110 degrees F (43 degrees C))', '0.5 cup white sugar', '0.33333334326744 cup warm water (110 degrees F (43 degrees C))', '2 tablespoons melted butter', '1 (.25 ounce) package active dry yeast', '3.5 cups all-purpose flour, or as needed', '3 tablespoons ground cinnamon', '1.5 tablespoons ground cardamom', '0.5 cup melted butter', '0.5 cup raisins', '0.5 cup chopped walnuts', '1 egg', '1 tablespoon water', '0.5 cup sliced almonds', '0.25 cup pearl sugar']
Instructions: ['Whisk together warm milk, 1/2 cup sugar, warm water, and 2 tablespoons melted butter in a large bowl until sugar is dissolved. Sprinkle yeast over the top and set aside for 5 minutes.', 'Once yeast is foamy, stir in flour, adding more as needed to form a stiff dough. When dough has pulled together, turn it out onto a lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 minutes. Place into an oiled bowl, cover with a cloth, and let stand in a warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.', 'Combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon, and cardamom in a small bowl  set aside.', 'Deflate dough and turn it out onto a lightly floured surface. Roll dough into a 9x13-inch rectangle and brush with 1/2 cup melted butter. Sprinkle with cardamom-sugar mixture, raisins, and walnuts. Roll into a log, pinch the edges closed, and place onto a parchment paper-lined baking sheet. Cover with a cloth and let stand in a warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.', 'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).', "Using a sharp knife, score the top layer of the roll with V-shapes that don't quite meet in the middle, the whole length of the roll. This will give the bread an attractive braided appearance, but can be skipped.", 'Beat egg with 1 tablespoon water in a small bowl until well combined  brush over the top of bread. Sprinkle with almonds and pearl sugar.', 'Bake in the preheated oven until bread is golden brown and sounds hollow when tapped on the bottom, 30 to 35 minutes. Cool completely on a wire rack before slicing.']

Name: Grilled Brined Pork Tenderloin
Author: OxPatchReb
Ingredients: [{'ingredient': 'water', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'gallon', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'salt', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'dark brown sugar', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'orange', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'misc': 'zested and juiced'}, {'ingredient': 'lemon', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'misc': 'zested and juiced'}, {'ingredient': 'lime', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'misc': 'zested and juiced'}, {'ingredient': 'cilantro', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'bunch', 'misc': 'chopped'}, {'ingredient': 'garlic', 'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'cloves', 'misc': 'smashed'}, {'ingredient': 'rosemary', 'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'sprigs', 'misc': 'chopped fresh'}, {'ingredient': 'thyme', 'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'sprigs', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'leaves', 'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'bay', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'whole black peppercorns', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'fennel seeds', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'coriander seed', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'whole cloves', 'quantity': '1.5', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'tenderloins', 'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pork', 'misc': 'trimmed and halved lengthwise 1 14 pound'}, {'ingredient': 'vegetable oil', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'misc': ''}]
Ingredients_Raw: ['0.5 gallon water', '0.5 cup salt', '0.5 cup dark brown sugar', '1 orange, zested and juiced', '1 lemon, zested and juiced', '1 lime, zested and juiced', '0.5 bunch cilantro, chopped', '6 cloves garlic, smashed', '2 sprigs fresh rosemary, chopped', '2 sprigs thyme', '4 bay leaves', '1 tablespoon whole black peppercorns', '1 tablespoon fennel seeds', '1 tablespoon coriander seed', '1.5 teaspoons whole cloves', '2 (1 1/4 pound) pork tenderloins, trimmed and halved lengthwise', '1 tablespoon vegetable oil']
Instructions: ['Warm water in a large pot over high heat. Add salt and stir to dissolve. Stir in brown sugar, orange, lemon, lime, cilantro, garlic, rosemary, thyme, bay leaves, peppercorns, fennel, coriander, and cloves. Bring to a boil, reduce heat to low, and cover. Let brine simmer for 20 minutes.', 'Fill a sink with ice water. Remove brine from heat and place pot into the sink. Cool, stirring, until brine reaches room temperature. Pour into a large plastic or glass vessel such as a 12-quart Cambro. Add pork tenderloin pieces. Cover and let soak, 6 hours to overnight.', 'Remove loins from brine and rinse. Let rest at room temperature for 30 to 45 minutes while you prep the grill. Preheat the grill for indirect heat at 275 degrees F (135 degrees C).', 'Place loins on the cooler side of the preheated grill and cook, rotating every 20 to 30 minutes, until an instant-read thermometer inserted into the centers reads 130 to 135 degrees F (54 to 57 degrees C), 35 to 40 minutes.', 'Brush vegetable oil onto loins and move over to the direct heat side of the grill. Sear until golden brown all over and the internal temperature just reaches 145 degrees F (63 degrees C), about 2 minutes per side. Remove loins from heat, place on a serving dish, and tent with foil. Let rest for about 5 minutes, then slice into 1/2- to 1-inch-thick medallions.']

Instructions: ['Gather all ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Name: Cheesecake Pops Recipe
Author: Cher
Ingredients: [{'ingredient': 'cream cheese', 'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'misc': 'softened 8 ounce'}, {'ingredient': 'sugar', 'quantity': '0.75', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'sour cream', 'quantity': '0.33333334326744', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'all-purpose flour', 'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'vanilla', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'salt', 'quantity': '0.25', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'eggs', 'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'sticks', 'quantity': '24', 'unit': 'lollipop', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'white confectioners coating', 'quantity': '10', 'unit': 'ounces', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'semisweet chocolate chips', 'quantity': '', 'unit': 'miniature', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'coconut', 'quantity': '', 'unit': 'toasted', 'misc': ''}]
Ingredients_Raw: ['3 (8 ounce) packages cream cheese, softened', '0.75 cup sugar', '0.33333334326744 cup sour cream', '3 tablespoons all-purpose flour', '1 teaspoon vanilla', '0.25 teaspoon salt', '3 eggs', '24 lollipop sticks', "10 ounces white confectioners' coating", 'miniature semisweet chocolate chips', 'toasted coconut']
Instructions: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).', 'Beat cream cheese and sugar in a large bowl until smooth. Mix in the sour cream and blend thoroughly, scraping down the sides of the bowl. Add the flour, vanilla, and salt and mix well. Add the eggs one at a time, blending thoroughly before adding the next egg, but do not overbeat. Pour batter into a 9-inch springform pan.', 'Bake in the preheated oven for 50 minutes or until the edges of the cake just begin to turn golden. Cool on a wire rack for 1 hour, then refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight.', 'Use a small cookie scoop to scoop out round balls of cheesecake. Roll them into 1 1/2-inch balls and place on a cookie sheet lined with waxed paper. Push a lollipop stick into each cheesecake ball. Place the tray in the freezer until firm, about 30 minutes.', "Melt the white confectioners' coating (or semi-sweet chocolate). Dip each cheesecake pop into the melted coating. Then dip into one of the toppings. Place on waxed paper until coating is set. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Store in refrigerator."]

Name: Creamy Salmon and Leek Pasta
Author: John Mitzewich
Ingredients: [{'ingredient': 'spaghetti', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': '', 'misc': '8 ounce'}, {'ingredient': 'butter', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'leek - light parts only', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'misc': 'rinsed and chopped'}, {'ingredient': 'to taste', 'quantity': '', 'unit': 'salt', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'white wine', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'lemon', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': '', 'misc': 'juiced'}, {'ingredient': 'creme fraiche', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'tarragon dijon mustard', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'cayenne pepper', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'misc': 'or to taste'}, {'ingredient': 'skinless', 'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'ounces', 'misc': 'boneless salmon sliced'}, {'ingredient': 'cilantro', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': 'or to taste chopped'}, {'ingredient': 'cayenne pepper', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'misc': ''}]
Ingredients_Raw: ['0.5 (8 ounce) package spaghetti', '1 tablespoon butter', '1 large leek - light parts only, rinsed, and chopped', 'salt to taste', '0.5 cup white wine', '0.5 lemon, juiced', '1 cup creme fraiche', '1 teaspoon tarragon Dijon mustard', '1 pinch cayenne pepper, or to taste', '6 ounces skinless, boneless salmon, sliced', '0.5 cup chopped cilantro, or to taste', '1 pinch cayenne pepper']
Instructions: ['Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook spaghetti in the boiling water, stirring occasionally until cooked through but firm to the bite, about 12 minutes. Drain and return to the pot.', 'Melt butter in a saucepan over medium heat. Cook and stir leek in butter until slightly softened, 6 to 7 minutes  season with salt. Pour white wine and lemon juice over the leeks, and bring to a boil while scraping any browned bits of food from the bottom of the pan with a wooden spoon. Simmer until most of the liquid evaporates, about 5 minutes.', 'Stir creme fraiche, mustard, and 1 pinch cayenne pepper into the leek mixture. Reduce heat to low and let cook until warmed, about 5 minutes. Add salmon to sauce  cook and stir until salmon starts to flake and is no longer pink in the center, 2 to 3 minutes. Remove pan from heat and stir in cilantro. Pour sauce over spaghetti  toss to coat. Garnish with a pinch of cayenne pepper.']

Ingredients_Raw: ['2 tablespoons peanut butter', '1 teaspoon Asian chile pepper sauce (such as sambal oelek), or to taste', '1 teaspoon lime juice', '0.5 cup carrots cut into thin matchsticks', '0.5 cup cucumber cut into thin matchsticks', '2 tablespoons jalapeno peppers cut into thin matchsticks', '1 tablespoon seasoned rice vinegar', '2 teaspoons fish sauce', '3 cloves garlic, minced', '2 tablespoons chopped fresh basil', '1.5 tablespoons coconut milk', '1 tablespoon dry bread crumbs', '2 teaspoons soy sauce', '0.5 teaspoon ground cumin', '0.25 teaspoon ground turmeric', '1 pound ground chicken', '1 pinch cayenne pepper, or to taste', 'salt', '4 hamburger buns', '0.25 cup cilantro leaves']
Instructions: ['Combine peanut butter, 1 teaspoon chili sauce, and lime juice in a small bowl  stir until thoroughly blended.', 'Combine carrot, cucumber, and jalapeño in a bowl  stir in vinegar and fish sauce. Set aside.', 'Combine garlic, basil, coconut milk, bread crumbs, soy sauce, remaining 1 teaspoon chili sauce, cumin, and turmeric in a bowl  mix in ground chicken until thoroughly blended (mixture will be very soft).', 'Fry a small piece of chicken mixture in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat until chicken is browned and no longer pink. Taste chicken piece  season chicken mixture with cayenne pepper and salt as needed. Do not eat raw chicken mixture.', 'Spoon 1/4 chicken mixture into the same skillet, forming a patty shape  cook until bottom browned, about 5 minutes. Flip and cook until browned and no longer pink inside, about 5 minutes more. Repeat with remaining chicken mixture to make 3 more patties.', 'Spread about 1 teaspoon peanut butter spread onto each bun half. Top each bottom bun with 1 chicken patty, 1/4 carrot slaw, and 1 tablespoon cilantro leaves. Place top buns on burgers  serve.']

Instructions: ['Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line a 9x13-inch baking pan with parchment paper.', 'Unroll 1 tube crescent roll dough  spread into the bottom of the prepared pan. Name: Homemade Cinnamon Rolls
Author: newyorkbaker<3
Ingredients: [{'ingredient': 'milk', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'water', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'butter', 'quantity': '0.25', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'unbleached all-purpose flour', 'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'white sugar', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'salt', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'rapid-rise yeast', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'misc': '25 ounce'}, {'ingredient': 'egg', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'butter', 'quantity': '0.25', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': 'softened'}, {'ingredient': 'light brown sugar', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'cinnamon', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'misc': 'ground'}, {'ingredient': 'cream cheese', 'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'ounces', 'misc': 'softened'}, {'ingredient': 'butter', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'misc': 'softened'}, {'ingredient': 'milk', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'vanilla extract', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'confectioners sugar', 'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'misc': ''}]
Ingredients_Raw: ['0.5 cup milk', '0.5 cup water', '0.25 cup butter', '3 cups unbleached all-purpose flour', '0.5 cup white sugar', '0.5 teaspoon salt', '1 (.25 ounce) package rapid-rise yeast', '1 egg', '0.25 cup butter, softened', '1 cup light brown sugar', '1 tablespoon ground cinnamon', '3 ounces cream cheese, softened', '1 tablespoon butter, softened', '1 tablespoon milk', '0.5 teaspoon vanilla extract', "2 cups confectioners' sugar"]
Instructions: ['To make the cinnamon rolls: Heat milk, water, and 1/4 cup butter together in a saucepan over medium heat until bubbling, about 5 minutes. Let cool to 120 to 130 degrees F (49 to 54 degrees C), 1 to 2 minutes.', 'Mix flour, white sugar, salt, and yeast together in a separate bowl. Mix egg into warm milk mixture.', 'Pour milk mixture and 1/3 of the flour mixture into a mixing bowl  beat using an electric mixer until moistened. Add remaining dry ingredients slowly until a dough has pulled together. Knead on a lightly floured surface for 8 minutes. Place in a covered bowl and let rise in a dry, warm place until doubled in size, 1 to 2 hours.', 'Punch dough down. Roll on a lightly floured surface into a 16x12-inch rectangle. Spread 1/4 cup softened butter evenly over dough. Mix brown sugar and cinnamon together in small bowl and sprinkle evenly over dough. Roll up from the short side  cut into 12 even rolls.', 'Mix brown sugar and cinnamon together in small bowl and sprinkle evenly over dough. Roll up from the short side  cut into 12 even rolls.', 'Place rolls into a greased 9x13-inch glass baking dish. Cover and let rise in a dry, warm place, 8 hours, to overnight.', 'When ready to bake: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).', 'Bake cinnamon rolls in the preheated oven until golden, about 17 minutes.', "Meanwhile, make the icing: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon butter, milk, and vanilla extract in a bowl with an electric mixer until creamy  slowly mix in confectioners' sugar until smooth.", 'Remove cinnamon rolls from the oven and flip out onto a cooling rack  let cool slightly, 5 to 10 minutes. Cover the tops of the rolls with icing.']

Name: The Best Sourdough Cinnamon Rolls
Author: kristi
Ingredients: [{'ingredient': 'all-purpose flour', 'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'fed sourdough starter', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'lukewarm milk', 'quantity': '0.75', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'white sugar', 'quantity': '0.75', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'instant yeast', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'butter', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': 'melted and cooled'}, {'ingredient': 'egg', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'misc': 'at room temperature'}, {'ingredient': 'salt', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'butter', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': 'melted and cooled'}, {'ingredient': 'brown sugar', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': 'or more to taste'}, {'ingredient': 'cinnamon', 'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'misc': 'ground'}, {'ingredient': 'confectioners sugar', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'pound', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'cream cheese', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'misc': '4 ounce softened'}, {'ingredient': 'butter', 'quantity': '0.25', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': 'softened'}, {'ingredient': 'vanilla extract', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'misc': ''}]
Ingredients_Raw: ['4 cups all-purpose flour', '1 cup fed sourdough starter', '0.75 cup lukewarm milk', '0.75 cup white sugar', '1 teaspoon instant yeast', '0.5 cup butter, melted and cooled', '1 egg, at room temperature', '0.5 teaspoon salt', '0.5 cup butter, melted and cooled', '1 cup brown sugar, or more to taste', '3 tablespoons ground cinnamon', "0.5 pound confectioners' sugar", '1 (4 ounce) package softened cream cheese', '0.25 cup softened butter', '1 teaspoon vanilla extract']
Instructions: ['To make the rolls: Combine 1 cup flour, starter, milk, white sugar, and yeast in the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the dough hook. Let stand until spongy and bubbling, about 5 minutes. Add 1/2 cup butter, egg, and salt  stir to combine. Beat in remaining 3 cups flour, 1 cup at at time, until a soft, slightly sticky dough forms.', 'Transfer dough to a floured work surface  knead until dough comes together, 3 to 5 minutes. Place in a greased bowl. Cover with plastic wrap  let rise until doubled in volume, about 1 hour.', 'Punch down dough and turn onto the floured surface. Roll into a square 1/4- to 1/3-inch thick. Spread 1/2 cup butter on top  sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon on top. Tightly roll up dough  pinch seam together.', 'Trim edges and cut log into 8 equal pieces using a sharp knife. Place rolls in the prepared pan. Cover with plastic wrap  let rise until not quite doubled in volume, about 45 minutes.', 'Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Grease a 9x13-inch baking pan.', 'Bake in the preheated oven until golden brown, about 35 minutes. Cool for 20 minutes before frosting.', "To make the frosting: Mix confectioners' sugar, cream cheese, 1/4 cup butter, and vanilla extract until frosting smooth and fluffy. Top cooled rolls with frosting."]
Nutrition: {'Calories': '894 kcal', 'Carbohydrates': '134 g', 'Cholesterol': '117 mg', 'Fiber': '4 g', 'Protein': '12 g', 'Saturated Fat': '22 g', 'Sodium': '427 mg', 'Sugar': '75 g', 'Fat': '36 g', 'Unsaturated Fat': '0 g'}

Name: Tres Leches (Milk Cake)
Author: Stephanie
Ingredients: [{'ingredient': 'all-purpose flour', 'quantity': '1.5', 'unit': 'cups', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'baking powder', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'unsalted butter', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'white sugar', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'eggs', 'quantity': '5', 'unit': '', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'vanilla extract', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'whole milk', 'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'sweetened condensed milk', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'misc': '14 ounce'}, {'ingredient': 'evaporated milk', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'misc': '12 fluid ounce'}, {'ingredient': 'heavy whipping cream', 'quantity': '1.5', 'unit': 'cups', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'white sugar', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'vanilla extract', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'misc': ''}]
Ingredients_Raw: ['1.5 cups all-purpose flour', '1 teaspoon baking powder', '0.5 cup unsalted butter', '1 cup white sugar', '5 eggs', '0.5 teaspoon vanilla extract', '2 cups whole milk', '1 (14 ounce) can sweetened condensed milk', '1 (12 fluid ounce) can evaporated milk', '1.5 cups heavy whipping cream', '1 cup white sugar', '1 teaspoon vanilla extract']
Instructions: ['Gather the ingredients.', 'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease and flour a 9x13-inch baking pan.', 'Sift flour and baking powder together  set aside.', 'Beat sugar and butter together in a large bowl with an electric mixer until lighter in color and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla  beat well. Add flour mixture, about 1/2 cup at a time, mixing until well blended.', 'Pour batter into the prepared pan.', 'Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean, about 30 minutes. Pierce cake all over with a fork  let cool to room temperature.', 'Mix whole milk, condensed milk, and evaporated milk together in a bowl.', 'Pour the whole milk, condensed milk, and evaporated milk mixture over the top of the cooled cake and allow to soak in.', 'Whip cream, remaining 1 cup of sugar, and 1 teaspoon vanilla in a chilled glass or metal bowl with an electric mixer until thick.', 'When milk mixture has soaked in, spread cream on top of the cake.', 'Keep cake refrigerated until ready to serve. Sprinkle ground cinnamon over top of the cake before slicing. Enjoy!']

Ingredients_Raw: ['3 (8 ounce) center-cut salmon fillets, with skin', '1 teaspoon garlic-pepper seasoning', '0.5 teaspoon dried dill weed', '1 tablespoon salt', '2 tablespoons olive oil', '2 tablespoons butter']
Instructions: ['Pat fillets dry with paper towels  set in a baking dish, skin-sides down. Sprinkle with garlic-pepper seasoning and dill. Flip fillets  generously rub salt only over skin. Cover the baking dish  set aside for 15 to 20 minutes.', 'Heat oil in a large cast-iron skillet over high heat until it just starts to smoke  reduce heat to medium-high and add butter. Add fillets, skin-sides down, as soon as butter melts. Cover the skillet  cook until fish flakes easily with a fork, 7 to 9 minutes, depending on thickness. Remove fillets with a metal spatula, halve each fillet, and serve immediately.']

Name: Ultimate Macaroni and Cheese
Author: McCormick Spice
Ingredients: [{'ingredient': 'elbow macaroni', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'misc': '16 ounce'}, {'ingredient': 'butter', 'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'flour', 'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'mustard', 'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'misc': 'ground mccormick®'}, {'ingredient': 'black pepper', 'quantity': '1.5', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'misc': 'coarse grind mccormick®'}, {'ingredient': 'garlic powder', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'misc': 'mccormick®'}, {'ingredient': 'salt', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'milk', 'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'sharp cheddar cheese', 'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'cups', 'misc': 'shredded'}, {'ingredient': 'panko bread crumbs', 'quantity': '1.5', 'unit': 'cups', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'paprika', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'misc': 'mccormick®'}]
Ingredients_Raw: ['1 (16 ounce) package elbow macaroni', '6 tablespoons butter', '6 tablespoons flour', '2 tablespoons McCormick® Mustard, Ground', '1.5 teaspoons McCormick® Black Pepper, Coarse Grind', '1 teaspoon McCormick® Garlic Powder', '1 teaspoon salt', '4 cups milk', '6 cups shredded sharp Cheddar cheese', '1.5 cups panko bread crumbs', '1 teaspoon McCormick® Paprika']
Instructions: ['Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (204 degrees C). Grease a 9x13-inch baking dish.', 'Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook elbow macaroni in the boiling water, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, about 8 minutes. Rinse under cold water. Drain well.', 'Melt butter in the same pot on medium heat  sprinkle with flour, ground mustard, black pepper, garlic powder, and salt. Cook and stir until well blended, about 2 minutes. Gradually stir in milk  cook, stirring constantly, until sauce begins to thicken, about 3 minutes.', 'Stir in cheese until melted and smooth. Off heat, gently stir in macaroni until coated. Transfer to the prepared baking dish. Combine panko and paprika  evenly sprinkle over top.', 'Bake in the preheated oven until bubbly and golden brown on top, 25 to 30 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.']

Name: Macaroons
Author: JOLLYGREEN23
Ingredients: [{'ingredient': 'whites', 'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'egg', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'salt', 'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'white sugar', 'quantity': '0.5', 'unit': 'cup', 'misc': ''}, {'ingredient': 'sweetened flaked coconut', 'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'misc': ''}]
Ingredients_Raw: ['2 egg whites', '1 pinch salt', '0.5 cup white sugar', '2 cups sweetened flaked coconut']
Instructions: ['Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Lightly grease a baking sheet.', 'Beat egg whites and salt together in a small glass, metal, or ceramic bowl using an electric mixer until soft peaks form. Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating at high speed until stiff peaks form  continue to beat until glossy. Fold coconut into egg white mixture.', 'Drop teaspoonfuls of egg white-coconut mixture onto the prepared baking sheet, spaced about 2 inches apart.', 'Bake in preheated oven until edges are light golden, about 12 minutes.']
